### [Isaiah Chapter 6](../../../bib/kjv/isa006.htm#001.md)

[Isaiah](../../../bib/kjv/isa001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">isa 6:0</span></span>

Overview

[Isa 6:1](../../../bib/kjv/isa006.htm#001.md), Isaiah, in a vision of the
Lord in his glory, [Isa 6:5](../../../bib/kjv/isa006.htm#005.md), being
terrified, has apprehensions removed; [Isa
6:8](../../../bib/kjv/isa006.htm#008.md), He offers himself, and is sent to
shew the obstinacy of the people unto their desolation; [Isa
6:13](../../../bib/kjv/isa006.htm#013.md), A remnant shall be saved.

